-- Inflation-Linked Gilt-Edged Sale Shows Weakest Demand Since October 2008
-- Paul Dobson
-- 2010-07-15T11:13:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/inflation-linked-gilt-edged-sale-shows-weakest-demand-since-october-2008.html

          
          
             (Corrects to show bonds for sale are due in 2022.)  
 Britain sold 1.2 billion pounds of
inflation-protected bonds maturing in 2022 at a yield of 0.947
percent. The debt drew bids 1.76 times the amount of securities
on offer, the lowest cover for this bond since October, 2008.  
          
          


  


        